      • TINYINT

        public static final SQLColumnType TINYINT
        TINYINT[(M)][UNSIGNED][ZEROFILL]

        空间: 1 字节 有符号值: -128 to 127 无符号值: 0 to 255

        最短的整数类型，M 为不影响值本身的可选的显示范围。

        public static final SQLColumnType BIGINT

        空间: 8 字节 有符号值：-9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,373,036,854,775,807 无符号值：0 to 18,446,744,073,709,551,615

        M 为不影响值本身的可选的显示范围。

        注意：较大值的算数运算可能会失败。

      • FLOAT

        public static final SQLColumnType FLOAT
        FLOAT[(M,D)][UNSIGNED][ZEROFILL]

        精确到小数点后 7 位，IEEE 754 单精度浮点值。

        M is the maximum number of digits, of witch D may be after the decimal point.

        Note: Many decimal numbers can only be approximated by floating-point values. See DECIMAL if you require exact results.

      • DOUBLE

        public static final SQLColumnType DOUBLE
        DOUBLE[(M,D)][UNSIGNED][ZEROFILL]

        精确到小数点后 15 位，IEEE 754 双精度浮点值。

        M is the maximum number of digits, of witch D may be after the decimal point.

        Note: Many decimal numbers can only be approximated by floating-point values. See DECIMAL if you require exact results.

      • DECIMAL

        public static final SQLColumnType DECIMAL
        DECIMAL[(M[,D])][UNSIGNED][ZEROFILL]

        M (precision): Up to 65 digits D (scala): 0 to 30 digits

        A fixed-point, exact decimal value. M is the maximum number of digits, of witch D may be after the decimal point. When rounding, 0-4 is always rounded down, 5-9 up ("round to wards nearest").

      • BIT

        public static final SQLColumnType BIT
        BIT[(M)] M: 1 (default) to 64

        A bit field type. M specifies the number of bits. If shorter values are inserted, they will be aligned on the least significant bit.

      • SERIAL

        public static final SQLColumnType SERIAL
        SERIAL 别名类型，指向: BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT UNIQUE

        public static final SQLColumnType BOOL
        BOOL 别名类型，指向: TINYINT(1)

        public static final SQLColumnType BOOLEAN
        BOOLEAN 别名类型，指向: TINYINT(1)

      • FIXED

        public static final SQLColumnType FIXED
        FIXED[(M[,D])][UNSIGNED][ZEROFILL] 别名类型，指向: DECIMAL

      • CHAR

        public static final SQLColumnType CHAR
        CHAR(M) M: 0 to 255 字符

        A character string that will require Mxw bytes per row, independent of the actual content length. w is the maximum number of bytes a single character can occupy in the given encoding.

      • VARCHAR

        public static final SQLColumnType VARCHAR
        VARCHAR(M) M: 0 to 65,535 字符

        A character string that can store up to M bytes, but requires less space for shorter values. The actual number of characters is further limited by the used encoding and the values of other fields in the row.

      • TINYTEXT

        public static final SQLColumnType TINYTEXT
        TINYTEXT Up to 255 字符

        A character string that can store up to 255 bytes, but requires less space for shorter values. The actual number of characters if further limited by the used encoding. v

      • TEXT

        public static final SQLColumnType TEXT
        TEXT[(M)] Up to 65,535 字符

        A character string that can store up to M bytes, but requires less space for shorter values. The actual number of characters if further limited by the used encoding. Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • MEDIUMTEXT

        public static final SQLColumnType MEDIUMTEXT
        MEDIUMTEXT Up to 16,777,215 字符 (16 MiB)

        可变长度的字符串。 The actual number of characters if further limited by the used encoding. Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • LONGTEXT

        public static final SQLColumnType LONGTEXT
        LONGTEXT Up to 4,294,967,295 字符 (4 GiB)

        可变长度的字符串。 The actual number of characters if further limited by the used encoding. Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • TINYBLOB

        public static final SQLColumnType TINYBLOB
        TINYBLOB Up to 255 bytes

        可变长度的字节数组。 Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • MEDIUMBLOB

        public static final SQLColumnType MEDIUMBLOB
        MEDIUMBLOB Up to 16,777,215 bytes (16 MiB)

        可变长度的字节数组。 Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • BLOB

        public static final SQLColumnType BLOB
        BLOB Up to 65,535 bytes

        可变长度的字节数组。 Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • LONGBLOB

        public static final SQLColumnType LONGBLOB
        LONGBLOB Up to 4,294,967,295 字符 (4 GiB)

        可变长度的字节数组。 Unlike VARCHAR this type does not count towards the maximum row length.

      • BINARY

        public static final SQLColumnType BINARY
        BINARY(M) M: 0 to 255 字节

        定长的字节数组。 Shorter values will always be padded to the right with 0x00 unit they fit M.

      • VARBINARY

        public static final SQLColumnType VARBINARY
        VARBINARY(M) M: 0 to 65,635 字节

        可变长度的字节数组。 The actual number of bytes is further limited by the values of other fields in the row.

      • JSON

        public static final SQLColumnType JSON
        JSON Limited to @@max_allowed_packet

        A data type that validates JSON data in INSERT and internally stores is in a binary format that is both, more compat and father to access than textual JSON. Available from MySQL 5.7.8

      • ENUM

        public static final SQLColumnType ENUM
        ENUM('member',...) up to 65,535 distinct members (<3,000 in practice) 1-2 bytes storage

        Defines a list of members, of witch every field can use at most one. Values are sorted by their index number (string at 0 for the first member).

      • SET

        public static final SQLColumnType SET
        SET('member',...) Range 1 to 64 members 1, 2, 3, 4 or 8 bytes storage

        A SET can define up to 64 members (as strings) of witch a field can use one or more using a comma-separated list. Upon insertion the order of members is automatically normalized and duplicate members will be eliminated. Assignment of numbers is supported using the same semantics as for BIT types.

      • DATE

        public static final SQLColumnType DATE
        DATE Range: 1000-01-01 to 9999-12-31

        Stores a date without time information. The representation is YYYY-MM-DD. The value is not affected by any time zone setting. Invalid value are converted to 0000-00-00.

      • DATETIME

        public static final SQLColumnType DATETIME
        DATETIME[(F)] Range: 1000-01-01 00:00:00.0 to 9999-12-31 23:59:59:999999 F (precision): 0 (1s) to 1 (1µs)

        Stores a date and time of day. The representation is YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS[.|*], I being fractional seconds. The value is not affected by any time zone setting. Invalid are converted to 0000-00-00 00:00:00.0. Fractional seconds were added in MySQL 5.6.4 with a precision down to microseconds (6), specified by F.

      • TIMESTAMP

        public static final SQLColumnType TIMESTAMP
        TIMESTAMP[(F)] Range: 1970-01-01 00:00:01.0 to 2038 01-19 03:14:07:999999 F (precision): 0 (1s) to 6 (1µs)

        Stores a date and time of day as seconds since the beginning of the UNIX epoch (1970-01-01 00:00:00). The values displayed/store are affected be the connection's @@time_zone settings. The representation is the same as for DATETIME. Invalid value, as will "second zero", are converted to 0000-00-00 00:00:00.0. Fractional seconds ware added in MySQL 5.6.4 with a precision down to microseconds (6), specified by F. Some additional rules may apply.

      • TIME

        public static final SQLColumnType TIME
        TIME[(F)] Range: -838:59:59.0 to 838:59:59.0 F (precision): 0 (1s) to 6 (1µs)

        Stores a time of day, duration of time interval. The representation is HH:MM:SS[.|*], being fractional seconds. The value is not affected by any time zone setting. Invalid values are converted to 00:00:00. Fractional seconds ware added in MySQL 5.6.4 with a precision down to microseconds (6), specified by F.

      • YEAR

        public static final SQLColumnType YEAR
        YEAR(4) Range: 0000, 1901 to 2155

        Represents a 4 digit year value, stored as 1 byte. Invalid values are converted to 0000 and two digit values 0 to 69 will be converted to years 2000 to 2069, resp. values 70 to 99 to years 1970 to 1999. The YEAR(2) type wars removed in MySQL 5.7.5

      • GEOMETRY

        public static final SQLColumnType GEOMETRY
        GEOMETRY

        Can store a single spatial value of types POINT, LINESTRING or POLYGON Spatial support in MySQL is based on the OpenGIS Geometry Model.

      • POINT

        public static final SQLColumnType POINT
        POINT

        Represents a single location in coordinate space using X and Y coordinates. The point is zero-dimensional.

      • LINESTRING

        public static final SQLColumnType LINESTRING
        LINESTRING

        Represents an ordered set of coordinates where each consecutive pair of two piints is connected by a straight line.

      • POLYGON

        public static final SQLColumnType POLYGON
        POLYGON

        Creates a surface by combining one LinearRing (ie. a LineString that is closed and simple) as the outside boundary with zero of more inner LinearRings acting as "holes".

      • MULTIPOINT

        public static final SQLColumnType MULTIPOINT
        MULTIPOINT

        Represents a set of Points without specifying any kind of relation and/or order between them.

      • MULTILINESTRING

        public static final SQLColumnType MULTILINESTRING
        MULTILINESTRING

        Represents a collection of LineStrings.

      • MULTIPOLYGON

        public static final SQLColumnType MULTIPOLYGON
        MULTIPOLYGON

        Represents a collection of Polygons. The Polygons making up the MultiPolygon must not intersect.

      • GEOMETRYCOLLECTION

        public static final SQLColumnType GEOMETRYCOLLECTION
        Represents a collection of objects of any other single- or multi-valued spatial type. The only restriction being, that all objects must share a common coordinate system.
